FBIS3-4512 "drchi062_a_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-062 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing Urges South African Parties To End Violence OW3103091994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0905 GMT 31 Mar 94 OW3103091994 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman today expressed the hope that all parties concerned in South Africa will take practical measures to end violence. Asked to comment on the recent aggravation of violence in South Africa at a weekly news conference here this afternoon, spokesman Wu Jianmin said that the recent aggravation of the violent conflicts in some regions of South Africa has aroused concern of the international community. "China always firmly supports the peace process of South Africa and hopes all parties concerned in South Africa will overcome their differences through negotiations, take practical measures to end violence, so as to ensure a smooth general election and join hands in working for a new South Africa in which all races are equal," Wu said.
